s"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[UK proposes plain vape packaging, flavour ban in crackdown on youth vaping]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132310044.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/uk-proposes-plain-vape-packaging-flavour-ban-in-crackdown-on-youth-vaping/articleshow/132310044.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/uk-proposes-plain-vape-packaging-flavour-ban-in-crackdown-on-youth-vaping/articleshow/132310044.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T16:36:29+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132310189,imgsize-795783.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[15 killed in Philippines landslides as Typhoon Bavi wreaks havoc, heads for Taiwan]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132309915.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Typhoon Bavi wreaked havoc in the Philippines, leading to tragic landslides that claimed the lives of at least fifteen people. The approaching storm caused significant evacuations and transport disruptions, as Taiwan braced for severe flooding and landslides, resulting in widespread school and business closures. Although weakening, the typhoon was poised to impact northern and eastern Taiwan before heading towards eastern China after affecting regions in Taiwan and Japan.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/15-killed-in-philippines-landslides-as-typhoon-bavi-wreaks-havoc-heads-for-taiwan/articleshow/132309915.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/15-killed-in-philippines-landslides-as-typhoon-bavi-wreaks-havoc-heads-for-taiwan/articleshow/132309915.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T16:22:49+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132309967,imgsize-65998.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[The deadly El Niño that killed millions in the 1870s could return in 2026]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132309279.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/in-the-1870s-one-of-historys-deadliest-el-nio-events-killed-millions-scientists-warn-the-upcoming-2026-event-could-rival-it/articleshow/132309279.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/in-the-1870s-one-of-historys-deadliest-el-nio-events-killed-millions-scientists-warn-the-upcoming-2026-event-could-rival-it/articleshow/132309279.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T16:13:04+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132309841,imgsize-186171.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Lego Trump funeral: Iranians target US president at Khamenei's burial]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132309267.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/lego-trump-funeral-iranians-target-us-president-at-khameneis-burial/articleshow/132309267.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/lego-trump-funeral-iranians-target-us-president-at-khameneis-burial/articleshow/132309267.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T16:06:46+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132309713,imgsize-60030.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Passenger nearly pulled out of Ryanair plane after cabin window breaks mid-flight]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132309272.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A Serbian tourist was nearly pulled from a Ryanair flight after a cabin window detached mid-air. Fellow passengers bravely pulled the man back inside the aircraft, which was returning to Thessaloniki. Oxygen masks deployed and a strong smell spread through the cabin following the decompression. The incident occurred over North Macedonia, possibly due to engine debris. Authorities are now investigating the cause of the window detachment.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/passenger-nearly-pulled-out-of-ryanair-plane-after-cabin-window-breaks-mid-flight/articleshow/132309272.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/passenger-nearly-pulled-out-of-ryanair-plane-after-cabin-window-breaks-mid-flight/articleshow/132309272.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T15:57:01+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132309375,imgsize-66400.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[This 143-million-year-old dinosaur discovered in Thailand, can rewrite parts of Jurassic history]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132308401.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/this-143-million-year-old-giant-dinosaur-uragasaurus-discovered-from-a-single-tiny-bone-in-thailand-can-rewrite-parts-of-jurassic-history/articleshow/132308401.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/this-143-million-year-old-giant-dinosaur-uragasaurus-discovered-from-a-single-tiny-bone-in-thailand-can-rewrite-parts-of-jurassic-history/articleshow/132308401.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T15:10:35+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132308482,imgsize-1723996.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[How a secret CIA operation in 1953 set the stage for decades of tension between Iran and United States]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132306948.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[US-Iran hostility stems from a 1953 CIA-backed coup which removed Prime Minister Mossadegh. Britain's oil dispute with Iran triggered the crisis and led to economic pressure. The Shah's rule, supported by the US, fostered growing opposition and anger. This historical distrust fueled the 1979 revolution and subsequent US embassy hostage crisis. Ongoing tensions persist over Iran's nuclear program and regional activities.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/how-a-secret-cia-operation-in-1953-set-the-stage-for-decades-of-tension-between-iran-and-united-states/articleshow/132306948.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/how-a-secret-cia-operation-in-1953-set-the-stage-for-decades-of-tension-between-iran-and-united-states/articleshow/132306948.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T15:25:25+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132307842,imgsize-174162.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meet Abraham de Moivre: Mathematician who calculated his own death based on his sleep pattern and was proven right]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132304699.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Abraham de Moivre, a prominent figure in French mathematics, is best known for his contributions to probability theory. An intriguing aspect of his legacy lies in his unique prediction about the day he would die, derived from the careful monitoring of his daily sleep duration. This systematic approach led him to a chilling conclusion about his life expectancy, sparking ongoing debate among scholars about its validity.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/meet-abraham-de-moivre-mathematician-who-calculated-his-own-death-based-on-his-sleep-pattern-and-was-proven-right/articleshow/132304699.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/meet-abraham-de-moivre-mathematician-who-calculated-his-own-death-based-on-his-sleep-pattern-and-was-proven-right/articleshow/132304699.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T16:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132304820,imgsize-87128.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[He was expelled from Church over child abuse, was reinstated and then he committed another heinous child sex crime]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132305043.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A former Mormon church leader has pleaded guilty to child sex crimes. Wade S. Christofferson admitted to coercing and enticing minors in federal court. He was previously removed and later reinstated by the church over earlier allegations. The investigation began after a sexually explicit FaceTime call with a child. Christofferson faces a mandatory minimum of ten years in prison.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/he-was-expelled-from-church-over-child-abuse-was-reinstated-and-then-he-committed-another-heinous-child-sex-crime/articleshow/132305043.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/he-was-expelled-from-church-over-child-abuse-was-reinstated-and-then-he-committed-another-heinous-child-sex-crime/articleshow/132305043.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T15:03:44+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132306127,imgsize-67916.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Indian embassy in Kuwait suspends normal passport, visa services till July 19: Only emergency cases allowed]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132307364.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/indian-embassy-in-kuwait-suspends-normal-passport-visa-services-till-july-19-only-emergency-cases-allowed/articleshow/132307364.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/indian-embassy-in-kuwait-suspends-normal-passport-visa-services-till-july-19-only-emergency-cases-allowed/articleshow/132307364.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T15:22:44+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132308704,imgsize-574957.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[This tiny mouse survives 7,000 metres on volcanoe where no mammal can stay alive: Scientists are investigating one of nature's greatest mysteries]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132306961.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The Andean leaf-eared mouse thrives at extreme altitudes, a feat previously thought impossible for mammals. This tiny rodent lives above 6,700 meters, enduring thin oxygen and brutal cold. Researchers found highland mice possess superior heat generation and efficient energy use for survival. Genomic studies reveal adaptations for processing plant chemicals and managing toxins. These findings offer potential insights for human medicine and understanding life's resilience.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/a-tiny-mouse-survives-near-7000-metres-on-volcanoes-and-scientists-are-trying-to-understand-how/articleshow/132306961.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/a-tiny-mouse-survives-near-7000-metres-on-volcanoes-and-scientists-are-trying-to-understand-how/articleshow/132306961.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T14:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132306960,imgsize-157774.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Six helicopters will drop 550 tons of poison on this island in the Indian Ocean: Why a project is spending $10 million on the exercise]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132304542.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Marion Island faces a massive mouse eradication effort using helicopters and poison. This project aims to protect native seabirds from the invasive rodent population. Helicopters will distribute 550 tons of rodenticide across the island's terrain. An aerial test is planned for April and May 2027 to evaluate the strategy. The eradication is essential for preserving the island's unique biodiversity.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/six-helicopters-will-drop-550-tons-of-poison-on-this-island-why-a-project-is-spending-10-million-on-this-exercise/articleshow/132304542.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/six-helicopters-will-drop-550-tons-of-poison-on-this-island-why-a-project-is-spending-10-million-on-this-exercise/articleshow/132304542.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T12:58:44+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132304564,imgsize-174710.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Japan kept a remote railway station open for years so one schoolgirl could get to class]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132304259.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A small Japanese railway station remained open for a single student for three years. The train schedule was adjusted daily to accommodate her school commute. This service continued until the student successfully completed her studies and graduated. After her graduation, the station was closed, ending its unique purpose. The story gained global attention as an example of customer-focused public transport.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/japan-kept-a-remote-railway-station-open-for-years-so-one-schoolgirl-could-get-to-class/articleshow/132304259.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/japan-kept-a-remote-railway-station-open-for-years-so-one-schoolgirl-could-get-to-class/articleshow/132304259.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T12:57:06+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132304853,imgsize-192308.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[In 1859, Australia released 13 rabbits for hunting. Decades later, they created one of the world’s worst invasive species crises]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132306692.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/in-1859-australia-released-13-rabbits-for-hunting-decades-later-they-created-one-of-the-worlds-worst-invasive-species-crises/articleshow/132306692.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/in-1859-australia-released-13-rabbits-for-hunting-decades-later-they-created-one-of-the-worlds-worst-invasive-species-crises/articleshow/132306692.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T14:30:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132307022,imgsize-149529.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Former Conservative MP, Reform UK spokesperson Ann Widdecombe dies aged 78]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132306235.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/former-conservative-mp-reform-uk-spokesperson-ann-widdecombe-dies-aged-78/articleshow/132306235.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/former-conservative-mp-reform-uk-spokesperson-ann-widdecombe-dies-aged-78/articleshow/132306235.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-10T13:14:55+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132306419,imgsize-607556.cms"/></item></channel></rss>